1. On-Device Smart Journal & Mood Analyzer
The Concept: A privacy-first digital diary that analyzes the user's emotional trends over time without ever sending their personal thoughts to a cloud server.

Core Features:

Rich Text Editor: Allow users to format text, add local images, and tag entries.
On-Device ML: Use TensorFlow Lite to run a sentiment analysis model directly on the phone to score the journal entry (e.g., positive, neutral, negative).
Mood Heatmap: A GitHub-style contribution calendar showing their mood history over the year.
Biometric Lock: Secure the app using the device's fingerprint or FaceID.

Why it's a great final year project:
It proves you can handle local state management, complex UI (heatmaps and rich text), native hardware APIs (biometrics), and on-device machine learning.
